VALUES
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_little_adventures','I’m off on little adventures',1,true,'ent_need_16_18_moving_bravely','I’m off on little adventures','Your toddler may be walking further, crouching for things and treating sofas, steps and laps as tiny routes. Safer movement ideas give all that energy somewhere useful to go, with balls to chase, push-pull play, music and low climbing that build confidence without turning the whole room into a risk zone.','for_your_child','cat_soft_graspable_balls','Soft balls to roll and chase','Soft Graspable Balls',1,'A soft ball gives your toddler a clear reason to move: step, squat, reach, fetch and try again. It can redirect throwing into something safer while building balance, coordination and shared attention indoors, in the garden or during a quick park reset.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A safe, simple gift if the family needs easy indoor or garden movement play.','You may already have a ball; this is about making it part of a turn-taking game.','Soft toddler balls','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_little_adventures','I’m off on little adventures',1,true,'ent_need_16_18_moving_bravely','I’m off on little adventures','Your toddler may be walking further, crouching for things and treating sofas, steps and laps as tiny routes. Safer movement ideas give all that energy somewhere useful to go, with balls to chase, push-pull play, music and low climbing that build confidence without turning the whole room into a risk zone.','for_your_child','cat_push_pull_toys','Push-and-pull toys','Push Pull Toys',2,'A steady push toy or short pull-along can make walking feel purposeful without rushing it. Your toddler gets to move, stop, turn and watch something follow, which adds a little problem-solving to whole-body practice.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if they are walking and do not already have something to push or pull.','Best if your toddler is already walking or close to it; skip if the house has enough moving toys.','Push-and-pull walkers or pull-alongs','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_little_adventures','I’m off on little adventures',1,true,'ent_need_16_18_moving_bravely','I’m off on little adventures','Your toddler may be walking further, crouching for things and treating sofas, steps and laps as tiny routes. Safer movement ideas give all that energy somewhere useful to go, with balls to chase, push-pull play, music and low climbing that build confidence without turning the whole room into a risk zone.','for_your_child','cat_low_climb_tunnel','Low climbing and crawl-through play','Low Climb Tunnel',3,'Climbing onto the sofa, crawling through a tunnel or stepping over a cushion can feel thrilling now. Low, supervised movement play gives your toddler a safer way to practise balance, strength and problem-solving without turning every chair into the main attraction.','for_your_child','setup','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',3,false,false,false,'Setup',NULL,'Start with cushions, a tunnel or a low sofa route before buying climbing equipment.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_little_adventures','I’m off on little adventures',1,true,'ent_need_16_18_moving_bravely','I’m off on little adventures','Your toddler may be walking further, crouching for things and treating sofas, steps and laps as tiny routes. Safer movement ideas give all that energy somewhere useful to go, with balls to chase, push-pull play, music and low climbing that build confidence without turning the whole room into a risk zone.','for_your_child','cat_music_dance','Music and dancing games','Music Dance',4,'Put on a song, pause for actions, copy their wiggle or hand them a simple shaker. Dancing and rhythm games give movement a playful pattern, while supporting listening, imitation and confidence when words are still catching up.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',4,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'Use pots, pans, clapping and favourite songs before buying instruments.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',2,true,'ent_need_16_18_two_hands','My hands are busy now','Your toddler may be doing more careful work with both hands: picking, fitting, pulling, stacking and starting again when it falls apart. The right challenges are satisfying without being fiddly, helping finger strength, focus and early problem-solving through little tasks they can repeat.','for_your_child','cat_threading_beads','Threading beads and chunky lacing','Threading Beads',1,'Large threading beads or chunky lacing cards can give both hands a clear job: hold, aim, push through and pull. It is a stronger challenge than simple posting, so choose big age-rated pieces and stay close.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A thoughtful gift only if the set is clearly age-rated and chunky.','If beads feel too fiddly, start with chunky rings or posting games first.','Chunky threading and lacing toys','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',2,true,'ent_need_16_18_two_hands','My hands are busy now','Your toddler may be doing more careful work with both hands: picking, fitting, pulling, stacking and starting again when it falls apart. The right challenges are satisfying without being fiddly, helping finger strength, focus and early problem-solving through little tasks they can repeat.','for_your_child','cat_stacking_pegboard','Stacking pegboards and block towers','Stacking Pegboard',2,'A pegboard or small set of chunky blocks lets your toddler build, topple, fit pieces into holes and try again. The value now is not owning blocks. It is adding a more precise hand challenge to familiar stacking and crashing.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if the family has only baby blocks and could use a new hand challenge.','If you already have blocks, this is about using them differently now.','Stacking pegboards or chunky blocks','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',2,true,'ent_need_16_18_two_hands','My hands are busy now','Your toddler may be doing more careful work with both hands: picking, fitting, pulling, stacking and starting again when it falls apart. The right challenges are satisfying without being fiddly, helping finger strength, focus and early problem-solving through little tasks they can repeat.','for_your_child','cat_shape_sorters_puzzles','Shape sorters and first puzzles','Shape Sorters Puzzles',3,'Simple knob puzzles, shape sorters and first matching boards help your toddler practise turning pieces around, looking for a fit and managing the tiny frustration of trying again. Keep pieces chunky and the challenge obvious.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','A strong gift choice for a child turning 18 months.','Useful if they are showing interest in fitting, posting or matching, not just chewing pieces.','First puzzles and shape sorters','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_busy_hands','My hands are busy now',2,true,'ent_need_16_18_two_hands','My hands are busy now','Your toddler may be doing more careful work with both hands: picking, fitting, pulling, stacking and starting again when it falls apart. The right challenges are satisfying without being fiddly, helping finger strength, focus and early problem-solving through little tasks they can repeat.','for_your_child','cat_velcro_pull_hide','Pull, stick and hide toys','Velcro Pull Hide',4,'Pulling felt, opening flaps, sticking pieces back on and hiding small characters gives your toddler a simple loop that feels almost impossible to resist. It builds finger strength and focus while staying more forgiving than puzzles with right answers.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if the pieces are chunky, soft and not easy to lose.','Try scarves, fabric scraps or a cardboard flap first if you want a no-buy version.','Velcro, flap and hide toys','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens',3,true,'ent_need_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens','Your toddler may keep doing the same action to see what changes: dropping, opening, rolling, hiding, tipping and doing it again. This is not just mess or repetition. It is early thinking, and simple cause-and-effect toys give that curiosity a clear, safe loop.','for_your_child','cat_ramp_rolling_toys','Ramp and rolling toys','Ramp Rolling Toys',1,'A ramp gives a beautifully obvious result: put the car or ball at the top, let go, watch it roll, repeat. Your toddler can test direction, speed and surprise while also practising waiting, reaching and following an object with their eyes and body.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A fun, stage-fit gift if the family likes cause-and-effect play.','You can test this first with a cardboard ramp and a large ball.','Ramp and rolling toys','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens',3,true,'ent_need_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens','Your toddler may keep doing the same action to see what changes: dropping, opening, rolling, hiding, tipping and doing it again. This is not just mess or repetition. It is early thinking, and simple cause-and-effect toys give that curiosity a clear, safe loop.','for_your_child','cat_posting_drop_boxes','Posting and drop boxes','Posting Drop Boxes',2,'Posting is still valuable, but the challenge can grow now: one-at-a-time dropping, matching a hole, tipping everything out and starting again. It turns a box or sorter into a repeatable thinking game.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',2,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'Try a tissue box, tub or cereal box with large safe objects before buying a toy.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens',3,true,'ent_need_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens','Your toddler may keep doing the same action to see what changes: dropping, opening, rolling, hiding, tipping and doing it again. This is not just mess or repetition. It is early thinking, and simple cause-and-effect toys give that curiosity a clear, safe loop.','for_your_child','cat_latch_busy_boards','Latches, doors and busy boards','Latch Busy Boards',3,'A simple busy board can channel the urge to poke, open, twist and repeat. It is most useful when the actions are chunky and obvious, not crowded with tiny fastenings that frustrate or create small-part worries.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if the board is simple, sturdy and age-rated.','Household containers, flaps and safe cupboards can offer the same idea first.','Latches, doors and busy boards','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens',3,true,'ent_need_16_18_cause_effect','I’m testing what happens','Your toddler may keep doing the same action to see what changes: dropping, opening, rolling, hiding, tipping and doing it again. This is not just mess or repetition. It is early thinking, and simple cause-and-effect toys give that curiosity a clear, safe loop.','for_your_child','cat_stacking_nesting_cups','Stacking and nesting cups','Stacking Nesting Cups',4,'Cups may already be in the house, but the play can change now: nesting by size, building little towers, hiding a toy underneath, tipping them out in the bath and copying a simple instruction.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','Only worth gifting if they do not already own stacking cups.','If you already have cups, reuse them for hiding, nesting and body-part instruction games.','Stacking and nesting cups','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_words_instructions','I’m finding my words',4,true,'ent_need_16_18_words_gestures','I’m finding my words','Your toddler may understand more than they can say, then suddenly pull your hand, point at a picture or try a new word. Books, songs, body-part games and naming walks help turn everyday moments into tiny conversations without making language feel like a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_first_word_picture_books','First-word picture books','First Word Picture Books',1,'First-word books work best when you pause and let your toddler point, try a sound or pull your hand back to a page. The book is only the prop. The value is the little back-and-forth around familiar things.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A safe, useful gift if it adds everyday words rather than noise.','If you have board books, choose ones with clear everyday pictures and lots of pauses.','First-word board books','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_words_instructions','I’m finding my words',4,true,'ent_need_16_18_words_gestures','I’m finding my words','Your toddler may understand more than they can say, then suddenly pull your hand, point at a picture or try a new word. Books, songs, body-part games and naming walks help turn everyday moments into tiny conversations without making language feel like a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_body_part_books_games','Body-part books and games','Body Part Books Games',2,'Pointing to nose, feet, tummy or hands can turn getting dressed, washing and reading into a word game. Body-part books or cards are useful because the same words keep coming back in routines your toddler already knows.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','Thoughtful if the child is starting to point or copy actions.','Use bath time, dressing and mirrors first; buy only if a clear book would help.','Body-part books and games','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_words_instructions','I’m finding my words',4,true,'ent_need_16_18_words_gestures','I’m finding my words','Your toddler may understand more than they can say, then suddenly pull your hand, point at a picture or try a new word. Books, songs, body-part games and naming walks help turn everyday moments into tiny conversations without making language feel like a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_songs_action_games','Songs and action games','Songs Action Games',3,'Songs with actions give your toddler a way to join in before they have all the words. Pause for their clap, point or sound, then repeat the bit they love. That repetition can make language feel playful rather than pressured.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',3,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'Use favourite nursery rhymes and family songs; props are optional.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_words_instructions','I’m finding my words',4,true,'ent_need_16_18_words_gestures','I’m finding my words','Your toddler may understand more than they can say, then suddenly pull your hand, point at a picture or try a new word. Books, songs, body-part games and naming walks help turn everyday moments into tiny conversations without making language feel like a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_naming_walks','Naming walks and object hunts','Naming Walks',4,'A slow walk can become a naming game: bin, dog, leaf, bus, door, shoe. Let your toddler point, wait, then name it back simply. It costs nothing and fits the stage where understanding is racing ahead of clear speech.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',4,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'This is a different way to use a walk you already do.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_copying_life','I’m copying real life',5,true,'ent_need_16_18_pretend_copying','I’m copying real life','Your toddler may now copy the tiny things you do: stirring, wiping, feeding a teddy, carrying a bag or pretending to talk. Simple props can make that copying feel meaningful, while supporting language, memory, care and early imagination through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_doll_soft_toy_care','Soft toy and doll care play','Doll Soft Toy Care',1,'Feeding, cuddling, washing or putting a soft toy to bed gives your toddler a safe way to copy the care they see every day. It can support language, memory and empathy without needing a complicated pretend world.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A warm gift if the family does not already have a soft doll or teddy they use for care play.','A favourite teddy can do this already; a doll is useful only if it opens up care play.','Soft dolls and care props','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_copying_life','I’m copying real life',5,true,'ent_need_16_18_pretend_copying','I’m copying real life','Your toddler may now copy the tiny things you do: stirring, wiping, feeding a teddy, carrying a bag or pretending to talk. Simple props can make that copying feel meaningful, while supporting language, memory, care and early imagination through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_toy_cups_spoons','Pretend cups, spoons and food','Toy Cups Spoons',2,'A spoon, cup, bowl or pretend snack can move easily between real routines and pretend play: feed teddy, stir soup, offer you a sip, then do it again. These small scenes support copying, words and early imagination.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if pieces are large, washable and useful for several kinds of pretend play.','Start with real safe spoons, bowls and an empty cup before buying a pretend set.','Pretend cups, spoons and food','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_copying_life','I’m copying real life',5,true,'ent_need_16_18_pretend_copying','I’m copying real life','Your toddler may now copy the tiny things you do: stirring, wiping, feeding a teddy, carrying a bag or pretending to talk. Simple props can make that copying feel meaningful, while supporting language, memory, care and early imagination through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_play_kitchen_household_props','Play kitchen and household props','Play Kitchen Household Props',3,'You do not need a full play kitchen for this stage. The useful bit is opening, stirring, wiping, serving and copying familiar routines. A few household props can give the same value if space or budget is tight.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','A bigger gift only if parents have space and would welcome it.','A full kitchen is a big buy; start with a pan, spoon and tea towel first.','Play kitchens and household props','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_copying_life','I’m copying real life',5,true,'ent_need_16_18_pretend_copying','I’m copying real life','Your toddler may now copy the tiny things you do: stirring, wiping, feeding a teddy, carrying a bag or pretending to talk. Simple props can make that copying feel meaningful, while supporting language, memory, care and early imagination through scenes they already recognise.','for_your_child','cat_toddler_bag_carry','Carry bags and little errands','Toddler Bag Carry',4,'A small basket or soft bag can turn routines into a job: carry socks, bring a nappy, pack a snack, move blocks back to a shelf. This gives independence a safe container and makes ''helping'' more than a cute moment.','for_your_child','setup','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',4,false,false,false,'Setup',NULL,'Use a basket, tote without long straps or soft storage tub before buying anything.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_mark_mess','I’m making my mark',6,true,'ent_need_16_18_mark_making','I’m making my mark','Your toddler may be ready to leave a mark: a crayon line, a handprint, a splash of water or a squish of dough. These early making moments are messy, but they build hand control, attention and confidence when the setup is simple and forgiving.','for_your_child','cat_chunky_crayons','Chunky crayons and first scribbles','Chunky Crayons',1,'Scribbling may still look like dots, lines and stabs at the page, but it is real hand-control practice. Chunky crayons and a big surface make it easier to grip, move and notice the mark they made.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A strong low-cost gift if parents are happy with supervised mark-making.','Try old envelopes, cereal boxes or a roll of paper before buying special pads.','Chunky crayons and first mark-making','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_mark_mess','I’m making my mark',6,true,'ent_need_16_18_mark_making','I’m making my mark','Your toddler may be ready to leave a mark: a crayon line, a handprint, a splash of water or a squish of dough. These early making moments are messy, but they build hand control, attention and confidence when the setup is simple and forgiving.','for_your_child','cat_water_drawing','Water drawing mats','Water Drawing',2,'A water mat, paving slab and brush, or dark paper with a wet sponge can let your toddler see cause and effect without a full paint setup. It is a gentle bridge between sensory play and drawing.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good for parents who want first marks with less cleanup.','You can try water painting outside with a brush before buying a mat.','Water drawing mats or water painting sets','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_mark_mess','I’m making my mark',6,true,'ent_need_16_18_mark_making','I’m making my mark','Your toddler may be ready to leave a mark: a crayon line, a handprint, a splash of water or a squish of dough. These early making moments are messy, but they build hand control, attention and confidence when the setup is simple and forgiving.','for_your_child','cat_play_dough_soft_clay','Soft dough and squish-safe sensory play','Play Dough Soft Clay',3,'Soft dough gives busy hands a different kind of challenge: press, poke, roll, tear and squish. Keep it simple, supervised and age-rated, and treat it as a short sensory moment rather than a full craft project.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if parents are open to supervised messy play.','Homemade dough or squishy food textures can offer a similar moment.','Soft dough and sensory play','thea','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_mark_mess','I’m making my mark',6,true,'ent_need_16_18_mark_making','I’m making my mark','Your toddler may be ready to leave a mark: a crayon line, a handprint, a splash of water or a squish of dough. These early making moments are messy, but they build hand control, attention and confidence when the setup is simple and forgiving.','for_your_child','cat_texture_tubs','Texture tubs and safe sensory baskets','Texture Tubs',4,'A basket with safe fabrics, chunky brushes, spoons, tubs or textured balls can become a small discovery tray. At this stage the value is naming, comparing, filling, emptying and choosing, not creating a perfect sensory bin.','for_your_child','setup','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',4,false,false,false,'Setup',NULL,'Use household objects first: flannels, tubs, wooden spoons and safe brushes.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_daily_practice','I’m taking charge at meals',7,true,'ent_need_16_18_self_feeding','I’m taking charge at meals','Meals may feel slower and messier because your toddler wants to do more themselves. Small changes, like a stable bowl, child-sized spoon, open-cup practice and safer snack prep, can help independence grow while keeping the routine more predictable and easier to repeat.','for_both','cat_open_cup','Open or free-flow cup','Open Cup',1,'An open or free-flow cup can help your toddler practise sipping, tipping and recovering from spills. The key is short, steady practice at real meals, not expecting neat drinking overnight.','for_both','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,false,false,'Parent buy',NULL,'You may already have one; this is about more regular, low-pressure practice.','Open cups and free-flow cups','conor','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_daily_practice','I’m taking charge at meals',7,true,'ent_need_16_18_self_feeding','I’m taking charge at meals','Meals may feel slower and messier because your toddler wants to do more themselves. Small changes, like a stable bowl, child-sized spoon, open-cup practice and safer snack prep, can help independence grow while keeping the routine more predictable and easier to repeat.','for_both','cat_first_spoons_bowls','Small spoons and stable bowls','First Spoons Bowls',2,'A toddler spoon and stable bowl can make self-feeding slightly less chaotic while still giving them the control they want. Expect spills. The aim is practice, not tidy meals.','for_both','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,false,false,'Parent buy',NULL,'Useful if mealtimes are becoming a constant wrestle over the spoon.','Toddler spoons and stable bowls','conor','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('16-18m','16–18 months',16,18,true,'ent_cluster_16_18_daily_practice','I’m taking charge at meals',7,true,'ent_need_16_18_self_feeding','I’m taking charge at meals','Meals may feel slower and messier because your toddler wants to do more themselves. Small changes, like a stable bowl, child-sized spoon, open-cup practice and safer snack prep, can help independence grow while keeping the routine more predictable and easier to repeat.','for_both','cat_finger_food_snack_prep','Finger-food and snack prep','Finger Food Snack Prep',3,'At this stage, snacks can become a language moment, a choice moment and a safety check. Preparing round, firm or slippery foods carefully lets your toddler practise feeding themselves without treating independence as a free-for-all.','for_both','setup','quick_checks','Quick checks',3,false,false,false,'Setup',NULL,'This is mostly a routine check, not a product to buy.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
