  ('22-24m','22–24 months',22,24,true,'ent_cluster_22_24_pretend_worlds','Pretend play gets richer',1,true,'ent_need_22_24_pretend_worlds','I’m making little worlds','Your toddler may be moving from copying one action to building tiny scenes: feeding a teddy, pouring pretend tea, putting animals in a bus or giving a doll a check-up. Simple props help them practise language, care and imagination through the routines they already know.','for_your_child','cat_small_world_vehicles_figures','Little worlds with vehicles and figures','Small World Vehicles Figures',6,'A few chunky people, animals or vehicles can help your toddler move beyond single-object play. They may start putting figures in a bus, feeding an animal or making a small scene happen again and again, which supports imagination and early story language.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',6,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good for a second birthday if pieces are chunky and age-fit.','Choose fewer, chunkier pieces rather than tiny sets.','Little worlds with vehicles and figures','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
