  ('22-24m','22–24 months',22,24,true,'ent_cluster_22_24_sort_match_build','Sorting, matching and building',3,true,'ent_need_22_24_sort_match_build','I’m sorting things my way','Your toddler may be ready for more deliberate thinking with their hands: sorting colours, matching shapes, stacking, twisting, threading or trying a puzzle again. These little challenges help them practise focus, control and problem-solving without turning play into a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_chunky_building_sets','Chunky building sets','Chunky Building Sets',4,'Blocks are still useful, but the job changes now. Your toddler may build a taller tower, line pieces up, add a vehicle or knock it down on purpose. That shift from banging to building gives old blocks a new role.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','A strong gift, but check what blocks they already own.','If they already have blocks, this is about using them differently now.','Chunky building sets','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
