  ('22-24m','22–24 months',22,24,true,'ent_cluster_22_24_sort_match_build','Sorting, matching and building',3,true,'ent_need_22_24_sort_match_build','I’m sorting things my way','Your toddler may be ready for more deliberate thinking with their hands: sorting colours, matching shapes, stacking, twisting, threading or trying a puzzle again. These little challenges help them practise focus, control and problem-solving without turning play into a lesson.','for_your_child','cat_tongs_scoops','Tongs, scoops and transfer play','Tongs Scoops',7,'Moving pom-poms, dry pasta or bath toys from one pot to another gives your toddler a satisfying little mission. It supports two-handed coordination, focus and early tool use with objects you may already have.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',7,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'Try household spoons and tubs before buying a set.','Tongs, scoops and transfer play','conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
