  ('22-24m','22–24 months',22,24,true,'ent_cluster_22_24_independence','Little independence at home',5,true,'ent_need_22_24_independence','I want to help properly','You may hear more ‘me do it’ at exactly the moments you are trying to leave the house. Small, repeatable routines can turn that push for independence into useful practice: washing hands, brushing teeth, putting things away, dressing with help and doing little jobs beside you.','for_your_child','cat_toothbrush_routine','Toddler toothbrush and teeth routine','Toothbrush Routine',6,'Your toddler may want to hold the brush, but an adult still needs to brush properly. A small brush, fluoride toothpaste and a repeatable song can make the routine calmer while keeping the health job clear.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',6,true,false,false,'Parent buy',NULL,NULL,'Toddler toothbrush and teeth routine','conor','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
