  ('28-30m','28–30 months',28,30,true,'ent_cluster_potty_toilet_practice','I’m noticing bathroom routines',7,true,'ent_need_28_30_potty_toilet_practice','I’m noticing bathroom routines','Some children around 28-30 months are ready for more potty independence; others are still watching, naming and practising the steps. The useful angle is readiness, relaxed repetition and clothing that makes small wins possible.','for_your_child','cat_potty','A potty to practise sitting','Potty',1,'A simple potty can sit in the bathroom so your toddler can notice, sit briefly and copy routines. Keep it calm and practical, not a test they have to pass.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,false,false,'Parent buy',NULL,'This is a parent buy, not a default gift.','Simple potties','conor','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
