  ('28-30m','28–30 months',28,30,true,'ent_cluster_potty_toilet_practice','I’m noticing bathroom routines',7,true,'ent_need_28_30_potty_toilet_practice','I’m noticing bathroom routines','Some children around 28-30 months are ready for more potty independence; others are still watching, naming and practising the steps. The useful angle is readiness, relaxed repetition and clothing that makes small wins possible.','for_your_child','cat_potty_training_books','Potty books and bathroom stories','Potty Training Books',4,'Potty books can introduce wees, poos, flushing and handwashing before pressure builds. Use them casually, especially if your toddler likes books and naming routines.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,false,false,'Parent buy',NULL,'Not a default gift unless the parent has asked for potty help.','Potty and bathroom books','conor','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
