  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_jigsaw_puzzles','First jigsaw puzzles','Jigsaw Puzzles',1,'A puzzle with a few chunky pieces can now be about strategy: turn it, compare it, try again. Choose a low-frustration design and let your child see the picture first.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',1,true,true,true,'Good gift','A reliable third-birthday gift when the piece count is age-fit.','Avoid baby peg puzzles if they already mastered them months ago.','First jigsaw puzzles','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_colour_matching_games','Colour and shape matching games','Colour Matching Games',2,'Matching the same colour, shape or picture helps your child practise looking carefully and explaining a choice. Keep the rule obvious and the win quick.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',2,true,true,true,'Good gift','A good small gift if the game is quick and simple enough to join.','A homemade sock-matching or lid-matching game can work too.','Colour and shape matching games','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_counting_sorting_loose_parts','Counting and sorting boxes','Counting Sorting Loose Parts',3,'Dropping, sorting and counting real pieces makes early number talk more concrete. The point is not formal maths; it is noticing more, less, same and different.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',3,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good if pieces are large, safe and useful in lots of games.','Household objects can do the job first; buy if a clearer challenge helps.','Counting and sorting boxes','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_memory_matching_games','Memory and matching games','Memory Matching Games',4,'A small memory game can support focus, turn-taking and noticing detail. Use only a few pairs at first so the game feels satisfying rather than like a test.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',4,true,true,true,'Good gift','A strong low-clutter gift for shared play.','Start with fewer pairs if the full game is too much.','Memory and matching games','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_first_rule_games','First games with simple rules','First Rule Games',5,'Games with one clear action, one turn and one finish can help your child practise waiting, following a rule and coping when the outcome is not theirs.','for_your_child','product_category','things_that_can_help','Things that can help',5,true,true,true,'Good gift','Good when the rules are genuinely simple and quick.','Choose a game the adults will actually play; avoid long board games.','First turn-taking games','both','See Ember Picks','product_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_puzzles_patterns_problem_solving','Puzzles, matching and little plans',3,true,'need_pattern_problem','I''m spotting patterns','At nearly three, puzzles and sorting are less about posting pieces and more about trying a plan: match the colour, notice the same, turn the piece, count the blocks, remember what comes next.','for_your_child','cat_blocks_building_challenges','Block builds with a plan','Blocks Building Challenges',6,'Blocks are not new, but the job can be. Try a bridge for the car, a tower as tall as teddy, or a house with a door. The value is planning, changing and trying again.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',6,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,'If you already have blocks, this is about using them differently now.',NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_feelings_turn_taking','Feelings, friends and turn-taking',4,true,'need_social_emotional','I''m learning the rules of people','Friend play may still be messy, but your child can start using words, waiting a little longer and noticing feelings. Small games and stories make rules feel concrete before real play gets heated.','for_your_child','cat_turn_taking_games','One-more-turn games','Turn Taking Games',1,'A throw, a roll, a card, a turn: short games let your child practise waiting without needing a long board-game session. Keep the pace quick and name what is happening.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',1,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
