  ('34-36m','34–36 months',34,36,true,'ent_cluster_feelings_turn_taking','Feelings, friends and turn-taking',4,true,'need_social_emotional','I''m learning the rules of people','Friend play may still be messy, but your child can start using words, waiting a little longer and noticing feelings. Small games and stories make rules feel concrete before real play gets heated.','for_your_child','cat_playdate_role_play','Playdate practice stories','Playdate Role Play',4,'Before a playdate, act out what might happen: two children want the same toy, someone says no, someone gets upset. Pretend makes the real moment less surprising.','for_your_child','activity','useful_ideas','Useful ideas',4,false,false,false,'Idea',NULL,NULL,NULL,'conor','Save idea','no_shop_actions'),
